parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition module can cause the engine to stall or die while driving, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies while driving
the ignition quits for no apparent reason
the vehicle is unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical fires can spread quickly and cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Flames or sparks emanating from the dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause the battery to drain, leading to engine stalling and loss of power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
Ignition coil failure can cause the engine to misfire or stall, leading to loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
Tire tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. The sudden loss of traction can result in rollovers, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: lumps or bulges on the tire surface.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper tire repairs can lead to tire failure, causing accidents, injuries, and fatalities. Inadequate repairs can allow air to migrate into the tire carcass, leading to tread separation.
symptoms: lumps or bulges on the tire surface.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or stop running, leading to safety risks, especially when it happens at night or on busy roads. Repeated instances of fuel system failure can also lead to financial burdens and emotional distress for vehicle owners.
symptoms: The vehicle stops running for no reason

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the fuel tank can lead to fuel leaks, which can cause fires, explosions, or other safety hazards. It can also lead to costly repairs and downtime for vehicle owners.
